claim.claim-text:
7. An apparatus for manufacturing a hemispherical solid immersion lens at a back surface of a semiconductor device, comprising: 
a pedestal; 
a grinding tool, fixed to said pedestal, for grinding the back surface of said semiconductor device, said grinding tool having a hemicircularly-cross-sectional groove perpendicular to a rotation axis of said grinding tool; 
a microscope, fixed to said pedestal, for detecting a predetermined location of said semiconductor device; and 
an alignment mechanism, movably mounted on said pedestal, for moving said semiconductor device in relation to said grinding tool and said microscope.

23. The method as set forth in claim 19, further comprising the steps of: 
coating a photoresist layer on the back surface of said semiconductor device; 
carrying out a photolithography process upon said photoresist layer by a double-side alignment exposure unit to form a photoresist pattern having a hole corresponding to said recess; 
etching said semiconductor device using said photoresist pattern as a mask; and 
removing said photoresist pattern after said semiconductor device is etched, 
so that said recess is formed in said semiconductor device.
